AB  - Amidst the global trend of digital transformation, electronic records are more than just a tool for information preservation; they serve as a foundational platform supporting data-driven decisionmaking. The state management of electronic records has emerged as a critical task aimed at building a robust data system and providing essential informational input for the management process. The authors' research focuses on four key aspects of state management of electronic records: (1) the development and promulgation of directives and guidelines for electronic records; (2) the management and organization of scientific research, and the application of science and technology in electronic records; and (3) the management and organization of personnel responsible for implementing electronic records. In Vietnam, Ho Chi Minh City, as a major urban center at the forefront of digital transformation across all sectors, has achieved notable successes in the state management of electronic records. However, the city's administration still faces significant challenges related to technological infrastructure, data security risks, and a deficit in awareness regarding the value of digital documents. This study provides an in-depth analysis and evaluation of the current situation, while also proposing solutions to enhance the effectiveness of state management of electronic records, bolster governance capacity, and contribute to the sustainable realization of digital transformation goals in Ho Chi Minh City. © 2025, Polish Mineral Engineering Society. All rights reserved.
